ZH: 我们必须忍受这种艰难的局面。
EN: We must endure this difficult situation.

ZH: 做父母的常常要忍受孩子的淘气行为。
EN: Parents often have to put up with their children's naughty behavior.

ZH: 他努力忍受着疼痛，不让任何人看到他的软弱。
EN: He tried to endure the pain, not letting anyone see his weakness.

ZH: 她是一个很坚强的女人，可以忍受各种各样的困难。
EN: She is a very strong woman, able to endure all kinds of difficulties.

ZH: 在这个严酷的社会环境中，我们必须忍受很多不公平待遇。
EN: In this harsh social environment, we must endure a lot of unfair treatment.

ZH: 虽然很痛苦，但我只能忍受，无法做出任何反应。
EN: Although it is painful, I can only endure it and not react.

ZH: 我们只有忍受一段时间，等到机会到来再做出反击。
EN: We can only endure for a while and wait for the opportunity to fight back.

ZH: 考试期间，我们必须忍受长时间的压力和焦虑。
EN: During the exams, we have to endure long hours of pressure and anxiety.

ZH: 他用坚强的意志忍受着每天的痛苦。
EN: He endures the pain every day with a strong will.

ZH: 她需要忍受一段时间的艰苦生活，才能实现自己的梦想。
EN: She needs to endure a period of hardship in order to achieve her dream.

ZH: 战士们忍受着重重的磨难，不畏艰难，坚韧不拔。
EN: The soldiers endure countless hardships, fear no difficulties, and remain steadfast.

ZH: 在这种恶劣的环境里，我们必须忍受噪音和恶臭。
EN: In this harsh environment, we have to endure the noise and bad smells.

ZH: 忍受疼痛是生活中的一部分，我们必须学会面对。
EN: Enduring pain is part of life and we must learn to face it.

ZH: 她的忍受能力非常强，从不抱怨生活中的困难。
EN: Her endurance is very strong, never complaining about the difficulties in life.

ZH: 在这种困境下，我们必须忍受现实，继续前行。
EN: In this predicament, we must endure reality and move forward.

ZH: 虽然局面很困难，但我们只能忍受，希望明天会更好。
EN: Although the situation is difficult, we can only endure and hope for a better tomorrow.

ZH: 忍受是一种能力，需要我们学会习惯和控制自己的情绪。
EN: Endurance is a skill that requires us to learn to adapt and control our emotions.

ZH: 在面对挑战时，我们必须学会忍受失败，不气馁。
EN: When facing challenges, we must learn to endure failure and not be discouraged.

ZH: 她只能忍受着孤独和无助的感觉，直到找到自己的出路。
EN: She can only endure the feelings of loneliness and helplessness until she finds her way out.
